        <name xml:lang="en">Thallium I</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimation based on fuel input data and emission factors from corresponding ecoinvent fuel combustion datasets (see "Extrapolations" comment). Internal fuels are represented by the calculated emissions but do not have the corresponding fuel input from technosphere, because they are supplied from within the system boundaries. The amounts of internal fuels used in the process are: Biogas and biosludge (0.266 GJ/t), Refuse derived fuel (RDF) (0.299GJ/t), other internal fuel (0.035 GJ/t). No proxy was available for the combustion of other internal fuels. Emissions from these internal energy generation processes are therefore only reflected in the key emission factors provided by the industry, other emissions constitute a data gap.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="5.46205570294218E-10" mu="-21.328025708672513" variance="0.04" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.05280000000000001"/>
